=head2 escapeXml()

Takes a single string argument, replaces "&", "<", and ">" with the appropriate
XML character entities, and returns the modified string.

=cut
sub escapeXml {
    my $text = shift;

    $text =~ s/&/&amp;/g;
    $text =~ s/</&lt;/g;
    $text =~ s/>/&gt;/g;

    return $text;
}
